Install Cucumber for rails


-----------------------------------------------------------

0. Install rvm, rails, ruby and create a project
-----------------------------------------------------------

	https://rvm.io/rvm/install/

	sudo apt-get install gcc g++ make build-essentials -y
	rails new blog	
		
-----------------------------------------------------------

1. Install cucumber-rails and rspec-rails
-----------------------------------------------------------

	https://github.com/cucumber/cucumber-rails  => Installation
	https://github.com/rspec/rspec-rails => Install

	sudo apt-get install libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev -y

	In Gemfile:
		group :test do
		  gem 'cucumber-rails', :require => false
		  # database_cleaner is not required, but highly recommended
		  gem 'database_cleaner'
		  gem 'rspec-rails'
		end

	bundle install


-----------------------------------------------------------

2. Hello World with cucumber
-----------------------------------------------------------
	
	http://cuke4ninja.com/sec_ruby_hello_world.html

	Follow the complete example in the page


Cucumber jargon 
